  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing HIV &amp; AIDS Epidemic Control Activity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project activities include identifying HIV-positive clients (especially those who do not know their status), providing them with life-saving antiretroviral therapy, supporting continuity in their treatment, and supporting adherence for clients whose treatment has been interrupted, in an effort to ensure HIV viral suppression to reduce AIDS-related deaths and further transmission of the virus.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the USAID-funded Advancing HIV &amp;amp; AIDS Epidemic Control (AHEC) Activity in South Sudan, IntraHealth is working with the government to increase the effectiveness and efficiency of the country&#x2019;s efforts toward HIV epidemic control. Applying a layered approach with local organizations and PEPFAR implementing partners, the South Sudanese government, and local communities, the AHEC Activity builds local capacity and resilience and adapts evidence-based HIV prevention, care, and treatment interventions for people living with HIV.</narrative>
  </description>
